---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Respecting User Time in Interaction Flow"
  description="Minimize unnecessary steps, interruptions, and wait states; keep the flow aligned with the user's goal and avoid repetitive or redundant prompts."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Respecting time in flow" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Inline, Non-Blocking</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Suggestions appear as you type. No "Submit" required for quick fixes; apply with one
            click. Background sync—no full-page reload.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >AI supports the flow instead of inserting extra steps or blocking the UI.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Clear Wait States</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Analyzing document… About 10 seconds. You can keep editing; we'll update when ready.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >User knows how long to expect and that they can do something else; no mysterious
            spinner.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Flow Friction (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >User must: confirm intent → choose model → confirm again → wait on full-page loader →
            then see result. Same confirmation dialog every time. No estimate for wait.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Extra steps and repeated confirmations slow the user down; opaque wait increases
            frustration.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Best Practices</b></mds-text>
          <div class="grid gap-300">
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Do:</b> Remember recent choices and skip redundant confirmations when safe</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Do:</b> Show progress or time estimates for operations that take more than a couple
                of seconds</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Don't:</b> Add steps or dialogs that don't clearly serve the user's goal</mds-text
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Keep the path to the user's goal short; use inline feedback and background work where
      possible.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Insert unnecessary confirmations, full-page loads, or repeated prompts that don't add value.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Show progress or time estimates for longer operations so users can decide to wait or switch
      context.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Leave users with an indefinite spinner or no indication of how long an action will take.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
